                                                SavePoint And RollBack Transaction
                                          ----------------------------------------------

Example with details: -   SavePoint and Rollback it does control the transaction.

                            public static void rollBackDetails() {
                                    Account acc = new Account(Name='RollBackTest');
                                    Contact con = new Contact(Email = 'sadiq@yahoo.com'); // DML Fail due to last Name.
                                   	SavePoint sp = Database.setSavePoint();
                                    try {
                              			  insert as user acc;  // account will be inserted.
                                   		insert as user con; // contact will be failed due to mandatory field. it will go to catch block
                                    }
                                    Catch(Exception ex) {
                                        System.debug('Exception occured in the transaction, details='+ex.getMessage());
                                        Database.rollBack(sp); // all transaction rolled back whatever dml placed between savepoint and rollback statement.
                                    }
                                }
